{"abstract":[{"text":"Some components can be used for ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"layouts"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"title":"Layouts","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png"}],"role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"anchor":"Colored-Surface","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Colored Surface"},{"tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Orange Business Tools","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredSurface_OrangeBusinessTools","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Sosh","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Sosh"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Wireframe","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"tabNavigator"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" suffix (for instance ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"colorBgDefaultEnabledMono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How it works","level":4,"anchor":"How-it-works","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"According to the color, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsUseMonochrome"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"oudsOnColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":4,"anchor":"How-to-use","text":"How to use"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"onStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.onStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.onStatusPositiveEmphasized)"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","level":4,"text":"Debuging contrast ratios"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", also named “RGAA”."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some components like ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used on "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","type":"reference"},{"text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratio.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratio.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"]},{"anchor":"Divider","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Divider"},{"anchor":"How-it-works","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"How it works"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSHorizontalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked vertically (e.g. in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VStack"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSVerticalDivider","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":": to separate elements stacked horizontally (e.g. in `HStack)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSDividerColor"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Horizontal","anchor":"Horizontal","type":"heading","level":5},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Orange"}]}]},{"title":"Orange Business Tools","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools"}]}]},{"title":"Sosh","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Sosh","type":"image"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Wireframe"}]}],"title":"Wireframe"}]},{"level":5,"text":"Vertical","type":"heading","anchor":"Vertical"},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Orange Business Tools","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_verticalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Sosh","type":"image"}]}],"title":"Sosh"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Wireframe","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Wireframe"}]},{"text":"How to use","anchor":"How-to-use","type":"heading","level":4},{"tabs":[{"content":[{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello world!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello world!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"]}],"title":"SwiftUI"},{"title":"UIKit (experimental)","content":[{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import OUDSComponentsUIKit","    ","\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","OUDSUIKit.createVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    ","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","OUDSUIKit.createHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)"]}]}],"type":"tabNavigator"}]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSButton":{"title":"OUDSButton","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" proposes layout with text only, icon only or text with icon."}],"kind":"symbol"},"component_verticalDivider_Orange":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/OUDSComponents\/component_verticalDivider_Orange.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":"An vertical divider in light and dark mode with Ora